{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, in tissue cellular neighborhoods identification, (Hu et al. 2024) developed the CytoCommunity algorithm, which uses graph neural networks to learn the mapping relationship from the cell phenotype space to the tissue cell neighborhood space.",
    "In particular, the application of the graph pooling technique enables the model to automatically align TCNs under different spaces during the learning process, which greatly facilitates the accurate identification of TCNs under specific conditions and opens up new perspectives for tissue biology research.",
    "In the frontier exploration of cheminformatics, graph pooling technology has become a key tool for solving complex chemical tasks such as molecular property prediction, compound Acute Dermal Toxicity (ADT) prediction, Odor Intensity (OI) prediction, and molecular graph generation.",
    "These methods have significantly improved the expressiveness and generalization capabilities of graph neural networks when processing chemical data by innovatively designing pooling strategies.",
    "Specifically, (Schweidtmann et al. 2023) proposed the Physical Pooling method, which carefully selects pooling functions by its profound physical insight."
  ]
}